    <name>Key Idea: Barriers to learning exist in the environment, not the learner. </name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;h4 style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.8rem;"&gt;​​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a data-sessionid="ea182251-f0b5-5e6e-c945-171f5e2b0cc7" data-shapeids="5" data-slide=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/octae-icon-keyideasforward.png" alt="" width="140" height="136" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anticipate diversity.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Many adult learners experience&amp;nbsp;disabilities. By focusing on identifying the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;barriers in the learning environment, you can design lessons, classrooms, and learning spaces that&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;support all learners, no matter whether they choose to disclose their individual disability &lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9688@$" target="_blank"&gt;(Gregg, 2012)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider-wave-1.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
